Please see below for details about Senior Stroll

Event: Leon Senior Stroll

Date: Thursday, May 21st

Time: 6:30 p.m.

Place: Parking Lots of Leon Elem, JH, & HS

All family and community members are invited to attend. Guidelines must be followed‚Ä¶

¬∑ Spectators will maintain social distancing regulations before, during, and after the event.

¬∑ Spectators may park in elementary, junior high or high school parking lots but must park in every other spot. This will be monitored by LISD Staff.

¬∑ Spectators will be allowed to sit on the back of their vehicles but must adhere to the social distancing guidelines.

¬∑ Spectators will not be allowed to congregate or interact with others that are not family. No gatherings or group pictures allowed on school property.

Anyone not following the social distancing guidelines may be asked to leave.

Masks are suggested but not mandatory.

post_text:
Leon ISD Graduation ceremonies for the Class of 2020 will be held Friday, May 29 at 7 p.m. at Cougar Stadium due to the fact that TEA regulations prohibits indoor ceremonies. Our office staff is currently contacting the parent's of the graduating seniors discussing initial plans and as the staff works through the planning process we will be able to have more information next week.

However, we know that attendance will be limited to comply with the governor‚Äôs executive order regarding social distancing. Because of the limited attendance, our plans are to have the commencement exercises available to view in real time on social media for those unable to attend.

Effective Monday April 6th, 2020 To minimize the risk of the spread of the COVID-19 Virus Leon ISD will be adjusting our Breakfast and Lunch pick-ups. We will still be at the Marquez and Jewett Baptist Churches from 11:00 to 12:00. However instead of handing lunches out Monday through Friday we will start next week handing out lunches Monday and Wednesday. Below breaks down our schedule.
Monday 11:00 -12:00 We will hand out Monday and Tuesday Meals
Wednesday 11:00 -12:00 We will hand out Wednesday, Thursday and Friday meals.
This will help limit the risk of transmitting the COVID-19 virus while still providing essential meals to our students.
If you have any questions please contact the school office.

As STAAR Tests are approaching we wanted to give parents some insight on how they can help their student be most successful.

Brains work better when‚Ä¶

‚Ä¢ The student has a full night sleep
o Turn off electronics early and tuck them in on time
‚Ä¢ The student has a normal breakfast
o Eating something ‚Äúspecial‚Äù may make for unsettled tummies, keep it simple
‚Ä¢ The student feels supported, without pressure.
o Test Anxiety is real for many so don‚Äôt stress the test, they will do their best.

5th Grade Math, April 9th
